parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and disintegration of the dashboard can cause sharp edges and loose debris, posing a risk of injury to occupants, particularly in the event of an airbag deployment. This can lead to increased severity of injuries in the event of an accident.
symptoms: dashboard material breaks down and turns to gravel
pieces of the dashboard fall off and drop into components beneath
sharp edges and points are exposed
dashboard material becomes brittle and fragile.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift linkage can cause the vehicle to roll away unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the transmission shifts into neutral without warning
the vehicle slides or moves without control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the LSD can cause catastrophic failure of the differential, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: causing small pieces of metal to break off and potentially lodge in gears

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle housing can cause oil leaks, leading to premature wear on the axle and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the rear axle
the whole rear axle assembly needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Frontal Collisions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in frontal collisions can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not provided with the necessary protection to absorb the impact.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in frontal collisions
despite the vehicle being equipped with airbags.
